references: Related: Res 10980, Res 11005, Res 11007, Res 11009, Res 11010
summary: An ordinance relating to the general municipal election to be held March 8, 1932; providing for the submission of proposed charter amendments contemplated by Resolution Nos 10980, 11005, 11007, 11009, and 11010; requiring City Comptroller and ex-officio City Clerk to certify to Election Board of King County, Washington, as required by law, said proposed amendments in the form of specified ballot titles and said amendments in the form of specified ballot titles and said amendments in full; and declaring an emergency.
